It's time for your food.

821
01:25:47,208 --> 01:25:49,419
Can I go outside
if I eat this?

822
01:25:49,544 --> 01:25:51,921
I don't know. You know how
you get sick in the afternoons.

823
01:25:52,046 --> 01:25:54,799
We'll see.

824
01:25:56,467 --> 01:26:00,304
Don't say that it tastes funny.
You know I don't like to hear that.

825
01:26:03,056 --> 01:26:07,227
Tami's mom called.

826
01:26:22,699 --> 01:26:25,076
You were
keeping her sick.

827
01:26:41,967 --> 01:26:44,678
You liked it,
she said.

828
01:26:47,722 --> 01:26:50,725
She looked out
for you.

829
01:26:50,850 --> 01:26:53,102
Is Kyra coming back?

830
01:26:56,272 --> 01:26:59,149
[Cole] Not anymore.

831
01:27:06,239 --> 01:27:08,491
[Woman] I think that's enough.
That's enough makeup.

832
01:27:08,616 --> 01:27:11,160
[Cole] Okay.

833
01:27:11,285 --> 01:27:14,955
- They're calling for the stable boy.
- We have to hurry !

834
01:27:18,500 --> 01:27:20,752
Who, uh--
Who were you talking to?

835
01:27:27,634 --> 01:27:30,636
Just practicing
my lines.

836
01:27:33,806 --> 01:27:36,558
Thanks for giving me this part,
Mr. Cunningham.

837
01:27:36,684 --> 01:27:40,395
You know, when I went to school
here, there was a terrible fire
in this section of the theater.

838
01:27:40,520 --> 01:27:42,481
They rebuilt
the whole thing.

839
01:27:42,606 --> 01:27:45,525
Yeah, I know.

840
01:27:47,110 --> 01:27:49,821
[Audience Sighing]

841
01:27:55,743 --> 01:28:00,622
Only he who is pure of heart
can take the sword from the stone.

842
01:28:00,747 --> 01:28:03,291
Let the boy try.

843
01:28:05,335 --> 01:28:07,462
